# Data Availability

The raw datasets used in this project are **not included** in this repository.

This repository is intended to demonstrate a fully reproducible analytical workflow while respecting the distribution policies of the original data providers. Users should obtain the original datasets directly from their official sources before reproducing the analysis.

---

## Primary Data Source

The primary dataset used in this project is the **Mission Antyodaya Village Facilities (2020)** dataset, accessed through the **SHRUG (Socioeconomic High-resolution Rural-Urban Geographic Platform)** metadata documentation maintained by the Development Data Lab.

**SHRUG Metadata (Mission Antyodaya Village Facilities, 2020):**

https://docs.devdatalab.org/SHRUG-Metadata/Mission%20Antyodaya%20Village%20Facilities%20%282020%29/Tables/antyodaya-metadata/

Users should obtain the data directly from the original source rather than through this repository.

The raw datasets are excluded from this repository because:

- They originate from external public data providers.
- Redistribution of large public datasets is unnecessary when they are already publicly accessible.
- Keeping the repository code-focused makes it easier to navigate, maintain, and reproduce.

Only scripts, documentation, and analytical outputs are distributed here.

The omission of raw data does **not** affect the reproducibility of the project, provided users obtain the original datasets from the sources listed above.

---

## Citation

If you use or adapt this repository, please cite both:

1. This GitHub repository.
2. The original Mission Antyodaya/SHRUG dataset and any additional data sources used in the analysis.
